name: language_html_data_active_unquoted_attribute_throw
description: |
  In an unquoted attribute value, this closes the current tag and inserts an SVG
  load handler that throws the standard canary error. It gives automated browser
  tests a high-signal failure for templates that omit attribute quotes.

  Correct quoting or DOM property assignment keeps it inert.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
pair:
  - with: ../attribute/unquoted-tag-breakout.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "active-xss-canary"
  - "html-attribute-context"
  - "unquoted-attribute"
  - "attribute-injection"
  - "throws-error"
---
x><svg onload="throw new Error('trickydata-xss-canary')"></svg><x x=
